  "contentHtml": "\n                                    \n\n                                                                            <p><img src=\"https://health.economictimes.indiatimes.com/Themes/Release/theme4/images/icons/et-default-user.svg\" alt=\"Anuja Jaiswal\">\n                                            \n                                        </p>\n                                                                        \n                                                                                    <ul>\n                                                                                                    <li>\n                                                                                                                                                                            <a>Anuja Jaiswal</a>\n                                                            \n                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        \n                                                                                                            </li>\n                                                                                                                                                    <li><a href=\"/agency/87654367/TNN\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">TNN</a></li>\n                                                                                            </ul>\n                                                                                <ul>\n                                                                                            <li>Updated On Jul 8, 2026 at 12:51 PM IST</li>\n                                                                                                                                            <li>\n                                                        \n                                                            \n                                                                Read by \n                                                            \n                                                            100 Professionals\n                                                        \n                                                    </li>\n                                                                                    </ul>\n                                    \n                                                                            \n                                                                        \n                                \n                                \n\n                    <!-- Display video article in news article for the custom next story -->\n                    \n                    <!-- Modifying the body placing embeds,promoslots,related etc.-->\n                                        <figure><img src=\"/images/default.jpg\" alt=\"\"></figure><p>New Delhi: The parliamentary standing committee on health and family welfare has recommended increasing the insurance cover under Ayushman Bharat-Pradhan Mantri Jan Arogya Yojana (<a href=\"/tag/pm-jay\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">PM-JAY</a>) from the existing 5 lakh to 10 lakh, saying the current limit is inadequate to meet the cost of several life-saving procedures, including liver transplants, complex cardiac surgeries and immunotherapy.</p><!-- PROMOSLOT_M --><p>The committee observed that advances in medical treatment have pushed the cost of several high-end procedures well beyond the scheme's existing coverage ceiling, leaving many beneficiaries vulnerable to substantial out-of-pocket expenditure despite being covered under PM-JAY. It recommended revising the coverage framework by introducing a differential treatment cost model for high-cost and complex procedures.</p><!-- PROMOSLOT_M -->\n                            <p>Advt\n                            </p>\n\n                              \n                                                         \n                        <p>\"The current 5 lakh coverage limit does not adequately meet the needs of most beneficiaries, as certain advanced interventions such as organ transplants like liver transplant, cardiac surgeries and immunotherapy treatments far exceed the threshold,\" the report said. It reiterated its recommendation to enhance the coverage limit to 10 lakh and create special high-cost packages under PM-JAY, supported through pooled financing, negotiated pricing with hospitals and manufacturers, and co-funding mechanisms with states.</p><!-- PROMOSLOT_M --><p>The panel said such a targeted enhancement would ensure that beneficiaries requiring expensive, life-saving procedures are not financially excluded while maintaining the fiscal sustainability of the scheme.</p><p>PM-JAY, the country's flagship govt-funded <a href=\"/tag/health+insurance\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">health insurance</a> scheme, currently provides cashless health cover of 5 lakh per family annually for secondary and tertiary care. It has been implemented in 35 states and Union Territories. As of January 31, 2026, the scheme had authorised 11.46 crore hospital admissions worth 1.69 lakh crore, while more than 43 crore Ayushman cards had been issued.</p><!-- PROMOSLOT_M --><p>The committee also sought stricter enforcement of the prescribed six-hour turnaround time for approving cashless treatment requests under PM-JAY. It recommended penalty provisions for hospitals or agencies responsible for undue delays, periodic audits of pre-authorisation workflows, expansion of auto-approval to more low-risk procedures and deployment of AI-enabled case tracking to speed up approvals.                    </p><!-- Category Most Read Placement -->\n                                                                    \n                                                                \n                                <ul>\n                                                                            <!-- <li>By <span>Anuja Jaiswal</span>,</li> -->\n                                    \n\n                                                                            <li>By\n                                                                                            <a>Anuja Jaiswal</a>\n\n                                                                                                                                                                                        , \n                                                                                    </li>\n                                                                        <li><a href=\"/agency/87654367/TNN\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">TNN</a></li>\n                                </ul>\n                                <ul>\n                                    <!-- <li> Updated On Jul 8, 2026 at 12:51 PM IST</li> -->\n                                    <li>Published On Jul 8, 2026 at 12:50 PM IST</li>\n                                    <!-- <li class=\"desktop-view\">2 min read</li> -->\n                                </ul>\n                            \n                                        \n\n                    \n\n                    <!-- Comment Section -->\n                                            \n                                        <!-- Comment Section -->\n\n                    \n                      \n    \n            <p>\n                </p><h2>Join the community of 2M+ industry professionals. </h2>   \n                <h3>Subscribe to Newsletter to get latest insights &amp; analysis in your inbox.</h3>\n            <p></p>\n\n            <!-- <figure class=\"top-newsletter-subs__icon-nl\" role=\"presentation\" aria-label=\"Newsletter icon\">\n                <img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https: